<br>
More tailored items, more quest items, more good items, more uber items.<br>
<br>
There are 'junk' item drops in various Luclin zones that make some of the uber stuff from the original game look lame.<br>
<br>
If you're fighting a wolf, why would it have coins?  That was one of the things that bugged me in the past expansions.  Things that have no place carrying coin, had coin.  Many of the lower level zones have primarily 'animal' type creatures that don't have any business carrying coin type loot.  <br>
<br>
The simple reason for not having an overabundance of coin drops is to keep inflation in check.  The more coins that exist in the economy, the less value they have.<br>
<br>
